    Verse: 4
Tags:
  - Depression/Despair
---
When we close our cheerful hearts, we shut the sunshine in. When we draw down
the shades, we darken our spirits. The dejected, depressed, damp-spirited
men -- the melancholy, dumpy people have had, and always will have, a hard
time of it.
